issue.title: Warn if unrecognised sections are present in bitcoin.conf
issue.body: Suggested by @MarcoFalke after #14627 and possibly #14420. We should warn if an unrecognised/incorrect section is present in bitcoin.conf. i.e `[testnet]` is present instead of `[test]`.

issue.title: RPC Does not work after upgrading for me
issue.body:
Ever since I upgraded to the latest version I cannot get bitcoin-cli to run.

**When I try**
`bitcoin-cli -rpcuser=charlie -rpcpassword=rv-aoHugIGt28UvY0888888wpTVXLkXYayymj2VXjE= -rpcport=8332 getblockchaininfo`

**I get a response:** 
```
error: Could not connect to the server 127.0.0.1:8332
Make sure the bitcoind server is running and that you are connecting to the correct RPC port.
```

I have not changed anything besides download source, compile, replace bitcoind and bitcoin-cli files and that's it.
Not sure why this would break all of a sudden.


**My bitcoin.conf file:**
```

testnet=1
daemon=1
maxconnections=10

# [configuration]
datadir=/mnt/volume-sgp1-02/.bitcoin/

# [wallet]

rpcclienttimeout=45

[testnet]
rpcport=8332
```

**Versions:**
```
Debian GNU/Linux 9 (stretch)
Bitcoin Core Daemon version v0.17.0.0-ge1ed37edaedc85b8c3468bd9a726046344036243
```

issue.title: Warn unrecognised sections in the config file
issue.body:
This PR intends to resolve #14702.

In the config file, sections are specified by square bracket pair "[]"$,
or included in the option name itself which separated by a period"(.)".

Typicaly, [testnet] is not a correct section name and specified options
in that section are ignored but user cannot recognize what is happen.

So, add some log-warning messages if unrecognized section names are
present in the config file after checking section only args.

note: Currentry, followings are out of scope of this PR.
1) Empty section name or option name can describe.
e.g. [] , .a=b, =c
2) Multiple period characters can exist in the section name and option name.
e.g. [c.d.e], [..], f.g.h.i=j, ..=k

issue.title: Check for invalid prefixes in config file
issue.body:
Gives a warning if an invalid section is used in the config file.

Related to #14702.
